# Hosting, routing, and prerender hygiene

## Rule

Hosting rewrites must not accidentally shadow API routes, static assets,
prerendered pages, proxy routes, or sitemap entries.

## Checklist

1. Specific rewrites/proxies come before SPA catch-all routes.
2. API routes are not captured by frontend fallback.
3. Prerendered/static routes are excluded from SPA fallback when required.
4. Sitemap, robots, canonical URLs, and public route lists match shipped routes.
5. Redirects preserve query params when those params carry state.
6. Security headers and CSP changes are minimal and documented.
7. Inline-script allowances do not accidentally allow inline event-handler
   attributes unless intentionally accepted.
8. Third-party script/font/image/connect domains are scoped to actual usage.
9. Local dev, preview, and production hosts are checked when routing differs.

## Pre-commit check

- [ ] Catch-all route is last.
- [ ] API/static/prerender routes still work.
- [ ] Sitemap/robots/canonical entries match.
- [ ] CSP is no wider than necessary.
